01:39.666 --> 01:42.167
Benson, would you make
us all some coffee, please.

01:42.168 --> 01:44.169
I can't.

01:44.170 --> 01:45.671
I beg your pardon?

01:45.672 --> 01:47.673
I can't.
I'm too depressed.

01:47.674 --> 01:49.174
I'll make the coffee, Chester.

01:49.175 --> 01:51.677
No, no, Mary, please.
This is Benson's job.

01:51.678 --> 01:54.680
I can't make no coffee.
Mrs. Tate's in jail.

01:54.681 --> 01:56.683
I can't make coffee.
I just gotta sit.

01:58.685 --> 02:01.687
You want coffee? You make it.

02:01.688 --> 02:03.188
I'll make the coffee.

02:03.189 --> 02:04.690
No, Eunice.
I'll make it.

02:04.691 --> 02:05.691
No, Mary.
You sit.

02:05.692 --> 02:07.192
All right, tell me how.
I'll make it.

02:07.193 --> 02:08.693
Come on.
I'll do it.

02:08.695 --> 02:10.195
No, Burt. You stay
with Chester.

02:10.196 --> 02:11.697
Let me, okay?

02:11.698 --> 02:13.699
No, Corinne. Your
coffee is terrible.

02:13.700 --> 02:14.700
Then don't drink it.

02:14.701 --> 02:15.701
I don't want coffee.

02:15.702 --> 02:17.202
I just want a Fresca.

02:17.203 --> 02:18.203
We could have tea.
Tea's easy.

02:18.204 --> 02:19.204
Get some whipped cream.

02:19.205 --> 02:20.205
I'll make some cappuccino.

02:20.206 --> 02:21.707
[ALL CHATTERING]

02:21.708 --> 02:22.708
All right, all right.

02:22.709 --> 02:24.209
Never mind the coffee.

02:24.210 --> 02:25.711
[RAISES VOICE]
Forget the coffee.

02:26.713 --> 02:29.214
Let's all just sit.

02:29.215 --> 02:31.217
That's what I said
in the first place.

02:34.721 --> 02:36.221
I checked out the jail,

02:36.222 --> 02:38.223
and according
to my calculations,

02:38.224 --> 02:43.729
a tank or a two-man bazooka team
could bring the wall down.

02:43.730 --> 02:47.232
Wonderful.

02:47.233 --> 02:50.235
Why don't you go outside
and check for enemy planes?

02:50.236 --> 02:51.737
Yep.

02:51.738 --> 02:55.741
Now, the important thing
is for us to be cool,

02:55.742 --> 02:57.743
to just sit and think,

02:57.744 --> 02:59.244
because we all know
in our heart of hearts

02:59.245 --> 03:02.748
that Jessica
is incapable of violence.

03:02.749 --> 03:05.751
Never in a million years,
under any circumstances,

03:05.752 --> 03:08.253
could Jessica possibly
have committed the crime.

03:08.254 --> 03:11.757
So with that in mind,
what we have to do now

03:11.758 --> 03:17.763
is to calmly and coolly
try to figure out...

03:17.764 --> 03:19.765
[RAISING VOICE]
which one of you rats did, huh?

03:19.766 --> 03:21.266
Which one?

03:21.267 --> 03:23.268
Which one of you stinking,
bloodthirsty Campbells...

03:23.269 --> 03:25.771
Campbells? Campbells?

03:25.772 --> 03:27.272
How about you Tates,
you embezzling thief?

03:27.273 --> 03:28.273
Don't start...

03:28.274 --> 03:29.775
Don't push me, Burt.

03:29.776 --> 03:31.276
Stop it!

03:31.277 --> 03:32.277
Hey! Hey!

03:32.278 --> 03:33.278
Come on!

03:33.279 --> 03:34.279
Get out of here.

03:34.280 --> 03:36.282
[CRASH]

03:39.786 --> 03:41.788
I ain't cleaning it.

03:49.796 --> 03:51.797
[MOANS] Oh.

03:51.798 --> 03:54.299
Burt! Look what you've done.

03:54.300 --> 03:56.301
I didn't touch him.

03:56.302 --> 03:57.803
Chester?

03:57.804 --> 03:58.804
Chester?

03:58.805 --> 03:59.806
Are you all right?

04:05.311 --> 04:07.813
Fine. I'm fine.

04:07.814 --> 04:10.816
I'm terribly sorry.

04:10.817 --> 04:12.818
Would you all excuse me
for a moment?

04:12.819 --> 04:14.320
Just go on
with what you're doing.

04:25.832 --> 04:28.333
Well, that's it. I can't go on.

04:28.334 --> 04:30.335
My life is over.

04:30.336 --> 04:31.336
My wife is in jail...

04:31.337 --> 04:33.839
the only woman
I've ever really loved.

04:33.840 --> 04:35.340
My career is over.

04:35.341 --> 04:37.843
I'll be in jail
for embezzlement.

04:37.844 --> 04:39.344
I can't go on.

04:39.345 --> 04:41.847
I might as well end it all.

04:41.848 --> 04:42.849
I'll leave a note.

04:44.350 --> 04:45.351
Paper. I need paper.

04:48.354 --> 04:52.357
Ah, the important thing
is how to do it.

04:52.358 --> 04:54.860
I want it quick, quiet,
and with no pain.

04:57.363 --> 05:00.866
I want it... pleasant.

05:00.867 --> 05:02.868
Ah, that's wonderful, Tate.
You want a pleasant suicide.

05:02.869 --> 05:04.370
Why don't you have it catered?

05:09.876 --> 05:12.378
There's not a piece of paper
in this kitchen.

05:22.388 --> 05:25.891
I never thought
I'd be writing a note like this.

05:25.892 --> 05:26.893
Never.

05:27.894 --> 05:29.394
Ahh, that doesn't look right.

05:29.395 --> 05:31.397
S-U-A-C-I-D-E?

05:33.399 --> 05:35.400
It's S-U-I, I think.

05:35.401 --> 05:38.403
No, that would be su-I-cide.

05:38.404 --> 05:39.905
Doesn't matter.

05:39.906 --> 05:41.406
They'll find a body
sprawled on the note,

05:41.407 --> 05:42.908
they'll figure it out.

05:54.420 --> 05:56.922
Perhaps it's not
the smartest thing

05:56.923 --> 05:58.423
I've ever done in my life,

05:58.424 --> 06:00.926
considering I'm not
too crazy about heights,

06:00.927 --> 06:02.428
but what can you do?

06:07.433 --> 06:09.935
Colonel! What happened?
Are you wounded?

06:12.438 --> 06:13.438
What do you want?

06:13.439 --> 06:16.441
A tank, sir. I need a tank.

06:16.442 --> 06:18.443
Take one. Take two.

06:18.444 --> 06:20.946
Thank you, sir.
Thank you very much.

06:32.458 --> 06:33.458
Chester...

06:33.459 --> 06:34.460
[CHESTER SCREAMS]

06:38.965 --> 06:39.965
Listen, Chester.

06:39.966 --> 06:41.967
Look, I just wanted
to apologize.

06:41.968 --> 06:43.468
I'm sorry.

06:43.469 --> 06:45.971
Oh, it's okay, Burt.

06:45.972 --> 06:46.973
All right.

06:49.475 --> 06:51.476
Chester...

06:51.477 --> 06:54.479
There's a knife in your door.

06:54.480 --> 06:58.984
Uh, yes, I know.
It makes a good handle.

06:58.985 --> 06:59.985
Well, I don't know.

06:59.986 --> 07:01.987
If you had to get
out of here in a hurry,

07:01.988 --> 07:03.488
you could leave
two fingers in the kitchen.

07:03.489 --> 07:05.490
It's dull.
Oh, it's fine.

07:05.491 --> 07:07.492
These are all dull.
All these knives are dull.

07:07.493 --> 07:08.493
They're fine, Burt.

07:08.494 --> 07:10.495
Come on.
Let me sharpen them for you.

07:10.496 --> 07:11.997
I got a wheel out in my truck.

07:11.998 --> 07:13.498
No, no. They're fine.
We like them dull.

07:13.499 --> 07:15.000
Yeah,
but they won't cut like this.

07:15.001 --> 07:16.001
We don't use them for cutting,

07:16.002 --> 07:17.502
we use them
for spreading butter,

07:17.503 --> 07:18.503
or for door handles.

07:18.504 --> 07:20.505
No, I tell you.
I'll make them as good as new.

07:20.506 --> 07:22.507
No, come here.

07:22.508 --> 07:24.009
Oh, well...

07:24.010 --> 07:25.510
The knives are gone.

07:25.511 --> 07:27.012
The oven's electric.

07:27.013 --> 07:28.513
What am I supposed to do?

07:28.514 --> 07:30.315
Jump in the blender
and puree myself to death?

07:32.018 --> 07:33.018
Do you realize

07:33.019 --> 07:34.019
that there's still a murderer

07:34.020 --> 07:35.521
running around loose?

07:47.533 --> 07:50.035
The Colonel
will be driving one tank.

07:50.036 --> 07:52.537
I'll be driving the other.

07:52.538 --> 07:55.040
We shall rendezvous at 0700,

07:55.041 --> 07:58.043
so everyone
synchronize your watches.

07:58.044 --> 08:00.046
It is now... 3-ish.

08:02.548 --> 08:05.050
I wonder where the murderer is.

08:05.051 --> 08:06.552
I bet right here.

08:09.055 --> 08:11.556
You think I did it, don't you?

08:11.557 --> 08:13.058
I know you think I did it.

08:13.059 --> 08:15.060
You've been staring
at me all day.

08:15.061 --> 08:17.062
Please. You?

08:17.063 --> 08:20.065
Everybody's looking at me
like I'm Jack the Ripper.

08:20.066 --> 08:21.066
Corinne,
they're not looking at you.

08:21.067 --> 08:22.567
They've been looking at me.

08:22.568 --> 08:24.069
I think it was the colored guy.

08:27.073 --> 08:28.573
We don't need him...

08:28.574 --> 08:30.075
Wait, wait, wait!

08:51.097 --> 08:55.100
Now all I have to do
is let go of the rope,

08:55.101 --> 08:56.102
and I'll be dead.

09:00.606 --> 09:04.609
I wonder
how good an idea this is.

09:04.610 --> 09:06.611
I mean, what will it solve?

09:06.612 --> 09:08.113
Ah, this is silly.

09:08.114 --> 09:10.115
Suicide is not the answer.

09:10.116 --> 09:11.116
Here you go, Chester.

09:11.117 --> 09:12.617
Sharper than
when you bought them.

09:12.618 --> 09:14.119
Here. Watch.

09:32.638 --> 09:34.139
[GRUNTING]

09:34.140 --> 09:35.640
To the right!
To the right!

09:35.641 --> 09:36.641
I'm doing it to the right.

09:36.642 --> 09:37.642
That's not the right, genius.

09:37.643 --> 09:39.644
That's the left.

09:39.645 --> 09:40.645
That's the right,

09:40.646 --> 09:41.646
because I write with this hand,

09:41.647 --> 09:43.148
and I'm a rightie.

09:43.149 --> 09:44.149
Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

09:44.150 --> 09:46.151
I wear my wedding ring
on my left hand,

09:46.152 --> 09:48.653
so how come it's on the
same side that you're pulling?

09:48.654 --> 09:49.655
Well...

09:51.157 --> 09:52.658
Well...

09:53.659 --> 09:55.160
Well?

09:55.161 --> 09:57.162
Because Danny's right
is your left.

09:57.163 --> 09:58.163
Right.

09:58.164 --> 09:59.664
So?
So?

09:59.665 --> 10:01.666
So when you said
"move it to the right,"

10:01.667 --> 10:03.168
he moved to his right,
which is your left.

10:03.169 --> 10:04.669
Right.

10:04.670 --> 10:07.672
Well, he should have known
when I say "move to the right,"

10:07.673 --> 10:09.674
I am referring
to the right which I can see,

10:09.675 --> 10:11.176
my right, which is his left.

10:11.177 --> 10:13.178
So when you say
"move to the right,"

10:13.179 --> 10:14.679
any idiot knows
you move to the left.

10:14.680 --> 10:16.681
You calling me
an idiot? Huh?

10:16.682 --> 10:17.682
Come on! Cut it out!

10:17.683 --> 10:19.184
I can't hold this anymore.

10:19.185 --> 10:20.685
All right, come on, now.

10:20.686 --> 10:21.686
Come on, to the right now,

10:21.687 --> 10:22.687
my right.

10:22.688 --> 10:23.688
Right.

10:23.689 --> 10:24.689
Ready? Go.

10:24.690 --> 10:26.691
Come on.

10:26.692 --> 10:27.692
Come in!

10:27.693 --> 10:29.194
It's stuck!

10:30.696 --> 10:31.696
Nothing.

10:31.697 --> 10:33.698
Well, it's different.

10:33.699 --> 10:35.200
When company comes over,

10:35.201 --> 10:37.202
they can sit down
before they come in.

10:37.203 --> 10:39.704
Ah, let it rest a while.

10:39.705 --> 10:41.206
It's probably swollen.

10:46.212 --> 10:49.214
Danny, this is a couch,
not a foot.

10:49.215 --> 10:51.217
Same principle.

10:52.218 --> 10:54.719
Whoo.

10:54.720 --> 10:55.720
Hey, Jodie...

10:55.721 --> 10:57.222
Hey, this is a nice...

10:57.223 --> 11:00.226
This is a really
nice place you got here.

11:02.228 --> 11:03.728
To the place.
To the place.

11:03.729 --> 11:04.729
To the place.

11:04.730 --> 11:05.731
Here you go.

11:07.733 --> 11:09.234
Makes me think of the first time

11:09.235 --> 11:10.735
I had my own place.

11:10.736 --> 11:12.237
That was a lot
different, though.

11:12.238 --> 11:13.738
For one thing,

11:13.739 --> 11:15.741
I didn't have
a couch in the door.

11:17.243 --> 11:18.743
Hi.

11:18.744 --> 11:19.744
Hi.

11:19.745 --> 11:21.246
Hey, Carol.

11:21.247 --> 11:22.747
Listen, uh, I think

11:22.748 --> 11:24.749
maybe you'd better leave
the furniture arranging

11:24.750 --> 11:25.750
to me.

11:25.751 --> 11:27.252
Carol and I are sharing
the apartment.

11:27.253 --> 11:28.253
Oh...

11:28.254 --> 11:29.254
Oh.

11:29.255 --> 11:31.256
Oh!
Oh-ho-ho!

11:31.257 --> 11:33.258
[HOWLING]

11:33.259 --> 11:35.260
It's platonic.

11:35.261 --> 11:37.762
Platonic?
Sounds kinky!

11:37.763 --> 11:39.264
We're roommates.

11:39.265 --> 11:40.765
That's roommates.

11:40.766 --> 11:42.267
All right.
That's roommates.

11:42.268 --> 11:43.768
That's all.

11:43.769 --> 11:45.770
All right. Room!
Room-room-room-roommates!

11:45.771 --> 11:47.272
Well, you call it what you want.

11:47.273 --> 11:48.273
That's what it is.

11:48.274 --> 11:49.774
Hey, come on, Jodie,
today's today.

11:49.775 --> 11:50.775
Once you get the door closed...

11:50.776 --> 11:51.776
It's not like that.

11:51.777 --> 11:52.777
I wish it were.

11:52.778 --> 11:54.279
Okay, it's all right, all right.

11:54.280 --> 11:55.780
I believe you.

11:55.781 --> 11:57.782
I always knew
he wasn't light in the loafers.

11:57.783 --> 11:59.284
Hi.
Oh.

11:59.285 --> 12:01.786
Hi.
Brought you a little house-warming present.

12:01.787 --> 12:04.289
Oh, I bet you did.

12:04.290 --> 12:06.291
It's... Who... I...
Who're you...

12:06.292 --> 12:07.292
I... What's...

12:07.293 --> 12:08.793
Dennis Phillips.

12:08.794 --> 12:10.295
That's Dennis Phillips,
the quarterback, right?

12:10.296 --> 12:11.296
Right.

12:11.297 --> 12:12.797
Oh, I'm so excited.

12:12.798 --> 12:14.299
What, like, you live in
this building, right?

12:14.300 --> 12:15.300
Do you know who this is?

12:15.301 --> 12:17.302
That's Dennis Phillips!
I know.

12:17.303 --> 12:18.803
And he brings you a fern!

12:18.804 --> 12:19.805
What a sweet guy.

12:22.808 --> 12:24.309
He lives in the building!

12:24.310 --> 12:25.810
Dennis Phillips lives
in your own building!

12:25.811 --> 12:26.811
I can't believe this.

12:26.812 --> 12:27.812
Listen, now,

12:27.813 --> 12:28.813
on Mondays, I'll come over,

12:28.814 --> 12:30.315
we'll discuss
the games together.

12:30.316 --> 12:32.317
Hey, I'm Burt.
How're you doing?

12:32.318 --> 12:33.818
[WHISPERING]

12:33.819 --> 12:34.820
What?

12:48.834 --> 12:51.336
But you're Dennis Phillips,
the quarterback.

12:51.337 --> 12:52.337
I know.

12:52.338 --> 12:53.838
Oh... Let go
of my hand!

12:53.839 --> 12:57.342
Listen, uh... Why don't we,
uh, get out of here?

12:57.343 --> 12:58.843
We got... The truck's
waiting for us downstairs,

12:58.844 --> 13:00.345
and, uh...

13:00.346 --> 13:01.346
And Jodie's got
all his friends here.

13:01.347 --> 13:02.847
He's got his girlfriend.

13:02.848 --> 13:04.349
He's got his boyfriend.

13:04.350 --> 13:05.851
Oh, let's get out...

13:14.360 --> 13:16.361
I'm also planning
on writing a book,

13:16.362 --> 13:17.362
on prison reform,

13:17.363 --> 13:18.863
but I don't really

13:18.864 --> 13:19.864
know what prison reform is,

13:19.865 --> 13:21.366
but since I'm gonna
be here so long,

13:21.367 --> 13:23.868
I'll certainly have
time to find out.

13:23.869 --> 13:27.872
So you see, Mary,
everything's fine.

13:27.873 --> 13:30.875
Oh, Jessie, you are incredible.

13:30.876 --> 13:34.379
You could find the good
in absolutely anything.

13:34.380 --> 13:36.381
Oh, well, Mary, I look for it.

13:36.382 --> 13:37.882
I look for it.

13:37.883 --> 13:39.884
Uh-oh.

13:39.885 --> 13:41.386
What is it?

13:41.387 --> 13:43.888
Oh, Mary...

13:43.889 --> 13:44.889
What is it, Jess?

13:44.890 --> 13:46.391
Sex.

13:46.392 --> 13:48.893
Sex?

13:48.894 --> 13:50.895
Mary, do you realize

13:50.896 --> 13:53.398
that prisons are full of men
and women

13:53.399 --> 13:54.900
who aren't getting any sex?

13:56.902 --> 14:00.906
Well, no wonder criminals say
"You'll never take me alive."

14:02.908 --> 14:05.910
Mary, what am I going to do?

14:05.911 --> 14:07.412
Well, uh, Jess,

14:07.413 --> 14:08.913
I think that you're just

14:08.914 --> 14:10.916
going to have to do without it.

14:14.420 --> 14:16.922
Are you crazy?

14:17.923 --> 14:19.424
I do.

14:19.425 --> 14:21.426
You still do?

14:21.427 --> 14:24.429
Well, at first, Burt couldn't,
and then I wouldn't,

14:24.430 --> 14:26.431
and then he could,
and now I would,

14:26.432 --> 14:28.933
but now he can't,
because he's never home.

14:28.934 --> 14:30.935
Where is he?

14:30.936 --> 14:32.437
Well, he's working very hard
lately,

14:32.438 --> 14:34.939
and by the time he gets home,
I'm asleep.

14:34.940 --> 14:36.941
I think I'll put these in water.

14:36.942 --> 14:39.944
Mary, I know
what you're thinking.

14:39.945 --> 14:41.946
But just because
Chester always told me

14:41.947 --> 14:43.448
he was working late

14:43.449 --> 14:44.949
when, actually,
he was fooling around,

14:44.950 --> 14:46.451
you don't have to think

14:46.452 --> 14:47.952
that Burt's doing
the same thing.

14:47.953 --> 14:50.955
I wasn't thinking
anything like that.

14:50.956 --> 14:51.956
Yes, you were.

14:51.957 --> 14:52.957
No, I wasn't.

14:52.958 --> 14:54.459
Of course you were!

14:54.460 --> 14:56.461
Oh, Mary, look,
in the first place,

14:56.462 --> 14:58.963
Chester could not possibly
have been working late,

14:58.964 --> 15:00.465
because he was a stockbroker,

15:00.466 --> 15:02.967
and, of course, the stockmarket
closes at 4 in the afternoon.

15:02.968 --> 15:05.970
Burt, on the other hand,
is in construction.

15:05.971 --> 15:10.975
Jessie... they don't
put up buildings at night.

15:10.976 --> 15:14.479
Well, Chester was always tired.

15:14.480 --> 15:17.482
Now, that's another
very good clue, Mary.

15:17.483 --> 15:18.983
Enormous fatigue.

15:18.984 --> 15:20.985
Burt's tired.

15:20.986 --> 15:22.487
Oh, well...

15:22.488 --> 15:24.989
That's because of all
of his physical activity.

15:24.990 --> 15:25.990
I bet!

15:25.991 --> 15:29.494
Mary, the man
works with his hands.

15:29.495 --> 15:31.497
I'm sure he does.

15:32.498 --> 15:34.999
Mary, Burt is not
having an affair,

15:35.000 --> 15:37.502
if that's what you're thinking.

15:38.504 --> 15:39.504
Jessica.
Hmm?

15:39.505 --> 15:41.005
How can they do this to you?

15:41.006 --> 15:43.508
I've never seen such
a miscarriage of justice.

15:43.509 --> 15:46.010
My poor, sweet Jessica.

15:46.011 --> 15:48.012
I love you...
hair!

15:48.013 --> 15:50.014
It's the most beautiful color
I've ever seen.

15:50.015 --> 15:51.516
What would you call it?

15:51.517 --> 15:52.517
Red.

15:52.518 --> 15:54.520
Oh, red.

15:56.021 --> 15:59.023
I think I'll go now.

15:59.024 --> 16:00.525
Uh...

16:00.526 --> 16:03.528
I'll see you tomorrow, Jess.

16:03.529 --> 16:05.531
Who says there's no sex
in prison?

16:11.036 --> 16:12.036
Jessica?

16:12.037 --> 16:13.037
Mm?

16:13.038 --> 16:14.038
I'll find him.

16:14.039 --> 16:16.040
I promise you, I will find him.

16:16.041 --> 16:17.041
Who?

16:17.042 --> 16:18.543
The killer.

16:18.544 --> 16:19.544
I'll find him.

16:19.545 --> 16:21.045
As God is my judge,
I'll find him.

16:21.046 --> 16:23.047
I'll go
to the ends of the earth.

16:23.048 --> 16:25.049
I'll sail every sea,
climb every mountain,

16:25.050 --> 16:27.051
look in every corner
of the world.

16:27.052 --> 16:32.056
Well, be extra safe
and get a typhoid shot.

16:32.057 --> 16:34.058
You will have a reaction to it,

16:34.059 --> 16:35.560
but it'll be worth it,

16:35.561 --> 16:37.061
because then you won't
have to worry

16:37.062 --> 16:38.062
about every little foreign thing

16:38.063 --> 16:40.065
you put in your mouth.

16:42.067 --> 16:45.570
Oh, Jessica, Jessica,
what are we going to do?

16:45.571 --> 16:47.572
You dear, brave, sweet woman.

16:47.573 --> 16:50.074
I love you...
eyes!

16:50.075 --> 16:52.577
"I love you, eyes"?

16:52.578 --> 16:54.079
See you tomorrow, Jess.

16:55.581 --> 16:58.083
I love you suit.

17:00.586 --> 17:02.587
How are you,
Mrs. Tate?

17:02.588 --> 17:03.588
Okay.

17:03.589 --> 17:05.089
I brought you some food.

17:05.089 --> 17:06.590
I know you can't eat the stuff

17:06.592 --> 17:07.592
they got here.

17:07.593 --> 17:08.593
Oh, thank you, Benson.

17:08.594 --> 17:10.094
That's very nice of you.

17:10.095 --> 17:12.096
Mm-hmm.
Are you okay?

17:12.097 --> 17:13.598
I'm fine.
You sure?

17:13.598 --> 17:14.598
Yes.

17:14.599 --> 17:16.099
Positive?

17:16.101 --> 17:17.102
No.

17:18.604 --> 17:21.105
I'm scared, Benson.

17:21.106 --> 17:23.608
I mean, every once in a while
it just kind of hits me:

17:23.608 --> 17:26.611
I'm on my way to the big home
for a...

17:26.612 --> 17:28.113
House. House.

17:29.615 --> 17:31.616
Big house.

17:31.617 --> 17:32.617
You're right.

17:32.618 --> 17:35.119
Yeah, for a murder
I did not commit.

17:35.120 --> 17:36.621
I mean, me, Benson.

17:36.622 --> 17:39.624
This is not Barbara Feldon
in that movie of the week...

17:39.625 --> 17:41.626
Eden, Barbara Eden.

17:41.627 --> 17:42.627
Right.

17:42.628 --> 17:44.629
And here I am,
and it isn't a movie,

17:44.630 --> 17:46.631
and it isn't Barbara Eden
in the slam,

17:46.632 --> 17:47.632
but me.

17:47.633 --> 17:49.635
Slammer.

17:51.136 --> 17:52.637
Time's up.

17:57.643 --> 18:01.646
Well, guess we'd better
say goodbye, Benson.

18:01.647 --> 18:03.147
Yeah, I guess.

18:03.148 --> 18:04.649
Goodbye, Benson.

18:11.156 --> 18:13.158
Oh, Benson...

18:14.159 --> 18:16.160
Not you.

18:16.161 --> 18:19.664
You've got to be strong.

18:19.665 --> 18:21.666
I mean, if you fall apart,

18:21.667 --> 18:24.168
there's not going
to be anybody left.

18:24.169 --> 18:26.671
Yeah.

18:26.672 --> 18:28.173
I'll see you soon.

18:30.676 --> 18:32.177
Goodbye, Benson.

18:37.683 --> 18:39.685
Goodbye, Mrs. Tate.

18:56.201 --> 18:58.202
Now, you promised.
Be nice.

18:58.203 --> 19:00.204
Hey, of course I'm gonna
be nice to her.

19:00.205 --> 19:01.706
What do you think
your mother is?

19:01.707 --> 19:02.707
I wouldn't be nice

19:02.708 --> 19:04.208
to the girl you're gonna marry?

19:04.209 --> 19:05.209
Oh...

19:05.210 --> 19:08.212
Dearie, I made some paté.

19:08.213 --> 19:10.215
I hope you like it.

19:11.216 --> 19:12.216
Most people claim

19:12.217 --> 19:14.719
that they spit
the paté out in France,

19:14.720 --> 19:16.721
once they've tasted mine.

19:16.722 --> 19:19.724
But what do they know
in East Orange, right?

19:19.725 --> 19:21.225
Honey, get me some napkins.

19:21.226 --> 19:24.228
Oh, what a lovely dress.

19:24.229 --> 19:27.732
Oh. Ooh, that's lovely.

19:27.733 --> 19:29.233
It's very lovely.

19:29.234 --> 19:32.236
You've ruined my life, you slut!

19:32.237 --> 19:33.237
I hate you!

19:33.238 --> 19:36.240
Oh, that paté should
lodge in your windpipe!

19:36.241 --> 19:38.242
Oh, you have ruined my life!

19:38.243 --> 19:39.744
Hey, Ma!

19:43.248 --> 19:45.750
I'm sorry.

19:45.751 --> 19:48.252
Oh... I lost my head.

19:48.253 --> 19:49.754
Oh, I'm sorry.

19:49.755 --> 19:51.255
I don't know what came over me.

19:51.256 --> 19:53.758
I have a kidney infection.

19:55.260 --> 19:56.260
Maybe that's it.

19:56.261 --> 19:59.263
Oh, all that poison
circulating in my body.

19:59.264 --> 20:01.766
Oh, honey, I'm sorry.

20:01.767 --> 20:03.267
Are you all right?

20:03.268 --> 20:04.268
[CROAKING] Yeah, I'm fine.

20:04.269 --> 20:05.770
Oh.

20:05.771 --> 20:07.772
So...

20:07.773 --> 20:10.274
I still don't know
very much about you,

20:10.275 --> 20:11.776
except what I've heard around...

20:11.777 --> 20:13.778
that your mother
is an adultress,

20:13.779 --> 20:15.279
and your father's an embezzler,

20:15.280 --> 20:16.280
and you bimbo,

20:16.281 --> 20:17.281
you've probably had more men

20:17.282 --> 20:18.282
than the whole Marine corp!

20:18.283 --> 20:19.784
You have ruined my life!

20:19.785 --> 20:21.786
You...

20:21.787 --> 20:24.288
Ma! Ma!

20:24.289 --> 20:25.289
[GRUNTING]

20:25.290 --> 20:26.290
You want my blessing?

20:26.291 --> 20:27.792
Is that what you came for?

20:27.793 --> 20:28.793
I'll give you my blessing.

20:28.794 --> 20:30.795
This is my blessing.

20:30.796 --> 20:32.296
May you never have
a happy moment again

20:32.297 --> 20:33.798
for the rest of your life.

20:33.799 --> 20:35.299
And if you marry,

20:35.300 --> 20:37.301
may you know no such thing
as peace and quiet.

20:37.302 --> 20:39.804
May you only know hardship
and suffering and loss,

20:39.805 --> 20:41.806
and may you know that,
to your dying day,

20:41.807 --> 20:43.808
whatever misfortunes happen

20:43.809 --> 20:45.310
are on your heads!

20:46.812 --> 20:47.812
[SLAMS DOOR]

20:47.813 --> 20:50.815
I can't believe it.

20:50.816 --> 20:52.316
Neither can I.

20:52.317 --> 20:55.320
Actually, she took it
better than I thought.

21:01.827 --> 21:04.328
Hello, hello...

21:04.329 --> 21:06.330
Jess...
How are you doing?

21:06.331 --> 21:08.332
You look beautiful.

21:08.333 --> 21:09.333
Oh, thank you.

21:09.334 --> 21:10.334
How are you, darling?

21:10.335 --> 21:12.336
Well, I'm a little nervous.

21:12.337 --> 21:13.838
I mean, after all,

21:13.839 --> 21:17.342
it isn't every day
that a girl gets sentenced.

21:20.846 --> 21:21.846
Hear, ye. Hear, ye.

21:21.847 --> 21:23.848
This court is now in session,

21:23.849 --> 21:25.851
the Honorable Anthony Petrillo
presiding.

21:26.852 --> 21:27.853
Everybody...

21:31.356 --> 21:32.357
Everybody, please stand.

21:33.859 --> 21:34.859
[GAVEL BANGS]

21:34.860 --> 21:36.862
Be seated.

21:39.364 --> 21:41.866
Will the defendant please rise?

21:41.867 --> 21:44.369
He just told me to be seated.

21:47.372 --> 21:48.873
Now, Mrs. Tate,

21:48.874 --> 21:51.375
you have been found guilty
of murder in the first degree.

21:51.376 --> 21:54.378
Have you anything to say
before I pronounce sentence?

21:54.379 --> 21:56.380
Yes.

21:56.381 --> 21:57.882
I didn't do this.

21:57.883 --> 21:59.885
I'm innocent.

22:02.387 --> 22:04.388
But...

22:04.389 --> 22:06.390
if the person is here

22:06.391 --> 22:08.392
who did it,

22:08.393 --> 22:12.897
please, help me.

22:12.898 --> 22:14.399
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

22:38.090 --> 22:42.094
All right, I'm going
to close my eyes now...

22:44.096 --> 22:47.099
Nobody will be embarrassed.

22:50.402 --> 22:51.602
Well, there doesn't seem to be

22:51.603 --> 22:54.105
a great traffic jam
to the bench,

22:54.106 --> 22:56.107
so I'll go on.

22:56.108 --> 22:57.608
Mrs. Tate,

22:57.609 --> 23:00.611
you have what some people
would perceive

23:00.612 --> 23:02.613
as certain advantages:

23:02.614 --> 23:04.615
you are white, and you are rich.

23:04.616 --> 23:07.118
If the sentence is light,

23:07.119 --> 23:09.120
the court will be besieged
with complaints

23:09.121 --> 23:11.122
from the poor and black.

23:11.123 --> 23:13.124
Therefore,

23:13.125 --> 23:15.626
in order
not to appear prejudiced,

23:15.627 --> 23:17.628
and to be fair
in the writing of a sentence,

23:17.629 --> 23:22.633
I've ignored the fact
that you are white and rich

23:22.634 --> 23:25.637
and have pretended
that you are poor and black.

23:30.142 --> 23:32.643
I sentence you
to 50 years in prison,

23:32.644 --> 23:35.646
eligible for parole in 25 years.

23:35.647 --> 23:37.148
I object, Your Honor.

23:37.149 --> 23:39.650
This sentence is unfair
and excessive.

23:39.651 --> 23:41.152
Objection overruled.

23:41.153 --> 23:42.654
Court is adjourned.

23:44.156 --> 23:46.158
[♪]

24:17.189 --> 24:18.689
Wait!

24:18.690 --> 24:20.691
Wait, everybody.
She didn't do it!

24:20.692 --> 24:22.693
[GAVEL BANGING]
Order in the court!

24:22.694 --> 24:24.696
Mr. Tate,
what are you talking about?

24:26.198 --> 24:27.198
I did it.

24:27.199 --> 24:28.199
[GALLEY GASPS]

24:28.200 --> 24:30.702
Isn't he sweet?

24:34.706 --> 24:36.207
No, I really did it.

24:36.208 --> 24:40.211
Mr. Tate,
that was a very nice gesture.

24:40.212 --> 24:41.712
Now, sit down.

24:41.713 --> 24:43.214
It wasn't a gesture.

24:43.215 --> 24:44.715
I murdered Peter Campbell.

24:44.716 --> 24:48.219
Mr. Tate,
the jury convicted Mrs. Tate.

24:48.220 --> 24:49.721
I don't care.

24:51.223 --> 24:53.724
I killed Peter Campbell.

24:53.725 --> 24:55.726
And I can prove it.

24:55.727 --> 24:57.228
[♪]

25:07.739 --> 25:09.240
Jessica...

25:12.244 --> 25:14.246
I hope you can understand.

25:15.747 --> 25:17.748
Understand?

25:17.749 --> 25:21.252
How can I understand, Chester?

25:21.253 --> 25:22.253
I mean,

25:22.254 --> 25:23.754
I was in jail for what I thought

25:23.755 --> 25:26.757
would be at least a lifetime,

25:26.758 --> 25:28.759
away from my family
and away from home.

25:28.760 --> 25:30.761
I find out
that my husband set me up,

25:30.762 --> 25:32.263
and you hope
that I can understand?

25:32.264 --> 25:33.764
Well, Chester,

25:33.765 --> 25:35.266
I just don't understand

25:35.267 --> 25:37.768
how you can expect me
to understand.

25:37.769 --> 25:42.273
No, you're right.
I can't expect you to.

25:42.274 --> 25:45.276
All I know is, Jess,
and I swear it...

25:45.277 --> 25:49.280
I don't remember anything
of what I did.

25:49.281 --> 25:53.284
I guess it was so horrible
that I blocked it out somehow.

25:53.285 --> 25:55.786
Not only do I not remember it,

25:55.787 --> 25:57.788
I still don't know why I did it,

25:57.789 --> 26:00.792
and I only remembered it
when the pot fell on my head.

26:03.295 --> 26:06.797
A pot fell on your head?

26:06.798 --> 26:10.301
Well, that's a long story, Jess.

26:10.302 --> 26:12.803
Chester, are you asking me

26:12.804 --> 26:14.305
to believe
that you killed someone,

26:14.306 --> 26:15.806
made it look like I did it,

26:15.807 --> 26:17.808
and you don't remember a thing
about what you did

26:17.809 --> 26:20.311
until a pot fell on your head?

26:20.312 --> 26:22.314
I guess that is asking a lot.

26:25.817 --> 26:27.318
I love you, Jess.

26:29.821 --> 26:31.322
Hello, everybody.

26:32.824 --> 26:33.824
See? I told you

26:33.825 --> 26:35.326
I wouldn't lose this case.

26:35.327 --> 26:36.827
Listen, I've got to
hand it to you, Tate.

26:36.828 --> 26:38.329
It was really big of you

26:38.330 --> 26:39.330
the way you spoke up.

26:39.331 --> 26:40.331
Really big.

26:40.332 --> 26:42.334
BAILIFF: Time's up,
Tate. Let's go.

26:44.836 --> 26:46.337
Chester...

26:46.338 --> 26:48.340
I'll see you tomorrow.

26:51.343 --> 26:52.843
I can't believe it.

26:52.844 --> 26:54.345
In one fell swoop,

26:54.346 --> 26:55.846
all our problems are over.

26:55.847 --> 26:57.848
You're out, he's in.

26:57.849 --> 27:00.851
You must handle his appeal.

27:00.852 --> 27:04.355
That's a good idea.
That way, he'll never get out.

27:04.356 --> 27:06.857
What do you mean?

27:06.858 --> 27:08.359
What mean is, darling,

27:08.360 --> 27:10.861
I'll make sure
he stays in prison forever.

27:10.862 --> 27:13.864
And then it's you and me,
just you and me.

27:13.865 --> 27:16.367
I don't believe it!

27:16.368 --> 27:18.869
Neither do I.
It's such incredible luck!

27:18.870 --> 27:21.372
Get out! Just...

27:21.373 --> 27:22.373
Get out!

27:22.374 --> 27:23.374
Okay.

27:23.375 --> 27:25.376
You've got a lot
on your mind right now.

27:25.377 --> 27:26.377
I'll tell you what.

27:26.378 --> 27:27.378
I'll call you later.

27:27.379 --> 27:28.880
See you, baby.

27:45.897 --> 27:48.399
What are you doing?
It's 3:00 in the morning.

27:48.400 --> 27:51.902
I can't sleep.
I'm making spaghetti.

27:51.903 --> 27:54.405
Spaghetti? You couldn't make
something simple?

27:54.406 --> 27:55.906
The refrigerator's
full of fruit.

27:55.907 --> 27:58.409
I'm really in the mood
for spaghetti.

27:58.410 --> 28:01.412
You want to talk about it?

28:01.413 --> 28:03.414
Spaghetti?

28:03.415 --> 28:04.915
What's bothering you, Billy?

28:04.916 --> 28:05.916
Oh, nothing.

28:05.917 --> 28:07.918
My dad killed someone
and framed my mom,

28:07.919 --> 28:08.919
but aside from that,
everything's fine.

28:08.920 --> 28:11.422
Listen, I'm not crazy
about your father.

28:11.423 --> 28:12.923
You know that.

28:12.924 --> 28:14.925
In fact, I think I'd be
the last person in the world

28:14.926 --> 28:16.927
to say anything nice about him.

28:16.928 --> 28:18.929
But I got to say this:
he did confess.

28:18.930 --> 28:20.931
He didn't let her fry.

28:20.932 --> 28:22.933
Big deal.

28:22.934 --> 28:24.015
So he's an honest murderer.

28:26.438 --> 28:27.938
What are you doing up?

28:27.939 --> 28:29.440
It's 3:00 in the morning.

28:29.441 --> 28:30.441
We're making spaghetti.

28:30.442 --> 28:31.942
We are not making spaghetti.

28:31.943 --> 28:33.444
You are making spaghetti.

28:33.445 --> 28:35.446
In the middle of the night?
What are you, crazy?

28:35.447 --> 28:36.447
Well, what are you doing?

28:36.448 --> 28:37.948
I'm making something to eat.

28:37.949 --> 28:39.450
What is this?
"Making something to eat."

28:39.451 --> 28:41.452
The refrigerator's full
of fruit.

28:41.453 --> 28:42.453
I don't want fruit.

28:42.454 --> 28:44.455
I'm making chocolate mousse.

28:44.456 --> 28:45.956
I thought you were on a diet.

28:45.957 --> 28:47.958
I am making dietetic
chocolate mousse.

28:47.959 --> 28:49.960
"Dietetic chocolate mousse."
Right.

28:49.961 --> 28:52.463
How do you make dietetic
chocolate mousse?

28:52.464 --> 28:53.464
It's easy.

28:53.465 --> 28:54.465
You make chocolate mousse,

28:54.466 --> 28:56.467
and then you don't eat it.

28:56.468 --> 28:57.968
You're not going to eat it?

28:57.969 --> 28:58.969
Not all of it.

28:58.970 --> 28:59.970
Anyway, what do I care?

28:59.971 --> 29:01.972
I'm too upset
to care what I eat.

29:01.973 --> 29:02.973
So I gain 200 pounds?

29:02.974 --> 29:04.475
My father killed someone,

29:04.476 --> 29:05.476
set up my mother,

29:05.477 --> 29:06.637
and I'm gonna count calories?

29:07.979 --> 29:08.979
Look at this one.

29:08.980 --> 29:09.980
She's so upset,

29:09.981 --> 29:12.483
she's not even cooking.

29:12.484 --> 29:13.484
What are you eating?

29:13.485 --> 29:15.486
I don't know.

29:15.487 --> 29:17.988
I think it's chili.

29:17.989 --> 29:19.990
You're eating cold chili?

29:19.991 --> 29:21.492
I don't care.

29:21.493 --> 29:23.494
I'm too upset to care.

29:23.495 --> 29:25.496
You know, some people,
when they're upset,

29:25.497 --> 29:26.497
can't eat a thing.

29:26.498 --> 29:28.499
I wish I was one of those.

29:28.500 --> 29:31.001
So do I.

29:31.002 --> 29:33.003
I can't believe it.

29:33.004 --> 29:34.505
It's like a nightmare.

29:34.506 --> 29:36.507
Daddy killed somebody.

29:36.508 --> 29:37.508
He's a murderer.

29:37.509 --> 29:40.010
Our father is a murderer.

29:40.011 --> 29:42.513
Well, strange people
do strange things,

29:42.514 --> 29:44.515
and your father's certainly
a strange man, so, you know...

29:44.516 --> 29:46.517
He's a murderer, Benson.

29:46.518 --> 29:48.519
I just wonder
if it's hereditary, you know,

29:48.520 --> 29:50.521
like, if it's in the genes.

29:50.522 --> 29:52.022
Like, I've already

29:52.023 --> 29:53.023
inherited a little asthma

29:53.024 --> 29:55.025
and a large chest.

29:55.026 --> 29:57.528
The idea of murder
doesn't thrill me.

29:57.529 --> 30:00.030
Hey, it could be worse.
You could be her.

30:00.031 --> 30:03.034
She has a lot of asthma
and a little chest.

30:04.035 --> 30:05.536
Oh!

30:05.537 --> 30:07.538
Everyone's up.

30:07.539 --> 30:08.539
Well, I...

30:08.540 --> 30:11.041
I just thought
that I'd come down

30:11.042 --> 30:13.544
and make something to eat.

30:13.545 --> 30:15.546
Have some fruit.

30:15.547 --> 30:17.047
No, I don't think so.

30:17.048 --> 30:19.049
I think I'm going
to make my own snack.

30:19.050 --> 30:20.551
Well, what are you doing?

30:20.552 --> 30:21.553
Me?

30:26.057 --> 30:30.060
I'm in the mood for turkey.

30:30.061 --> 30:31.061
But it's frozen.

30:31.062 --> 30:33.564
Well, it'll thaw out
when I cook it.

30:33.565 --> 30:35.566
Yeah, in about two days.

30:35.567 --> 30:39.069
Oh, well, I wanted something
to eat before then.

30:39.070 --> 30:40.571
Well, have some fruit.

30:40.572 --> 30:42.072
No, I don't want any fruit.

30:42.073 --> 30:43.574
You're really pushing the fruit.

30:43.575 --> 30:45.075
Well, it's just that I buy it

30:45.076 --> 30:46.076
and nobody eats it.

30:46.077 --> 30:48.078
In a few days,
I open the refrigerator

30:48.079 --> 30:51.082
and it's full of little
brown, furry, wrinkled things.

30:52.584 --> 30:56.087
Billy, did you put your hamsters
in the refrigerator?

30:58.089 --> 31:00.090
Rotten fruit
is in the refrigerator.

31:00.091 --> 31:01.592
Rotten fruit?

31:01.593 --> 31:04.596
Benson, you mustn't buy
rotten fruit.

31:06.598 --> 31:08.599
Well, on second thought,

31:08.600 --> 31:10.100
I don't think I'll eat anything.

31:10.101 --> 31:11.602
I lost my appetite.

31:13.605 --> 31:17.107
Guess you're all waiting
for me to say something.

31:17.108 --> 31:19.110
I'm waiting for you
to give me the turkey.

31:25.617 --> 31:27.618
I don't know what to say

31:27.619 --> 31:30.621
except that, no matter what,

31:30.622 --> 31:33.624
I still love your father.

31:33.625 --> 31:37.628
But, Ma, he killed somebody
and he framed you.

31:37.629 --> 31:40.131
Well, it certainly
does look that way.

31:42.133 --> 31:46.136
Oh, I wish I were Donna Reed.

31:46.137 --> 31:47.638
I mean, Donna Reed

31:47.639 --> 31:50.140
would have something
wonderful to say.

31:50.141 --> 31:52.643
Or even Shirley Jones,
for that matter.

31:52.644 --> 31:54.144
She'd have something
just as good to say,

31:54.145 --> 31:57.147
and maybe even
fresh-baked cookies.

31:57.148 --> 31:58.649
Or Loretta Young.

31:58.650 --> 32:00.150
Of course, she wouldn't

32:00.151 --> 32:01.151
have anything wonderful to say,

32:01.152 --> 32:04.154
but she would make
a stunning entrance.

32:04.155 --> 32:06.657
Well, I'm going to make
a stunning exit.

32:06.658 --> 32:07.658
Good night.

32:07.659 --> 32:08.660
Good night, Benson.

32:13.164 --> 32:16.166
I just don't believe
that it's as simple as it seems.

32:16.167 --> 32:17.167
I mean, I don't believe

32:17.168 --> 32:19.169
that you live half your life
with a man

32:19.170 --> 32:21.171
and not really know him.

32:21.172 --> 32:22.673
Your father is a good man.

32:22.674 --> 32:24.174
You all loved him
when he was here

32:24.175 --> 32:25.676
for birthdays and Christmas.

32:25.677 --> 32:27.177
You loved him

32:27.178 --> 32:30.180
when he took you
to the ballet...

32:30.181 --> 32:34.184
when he bought you
your first tie...

32:34.185 --> 32:35.686
you loved him
when he taught you to swim

32:35.687 --> 32:38.188
and drive the car.

32:38.189 --> 32:39.189
Remember?

32:39.190 --> 32:42.192
I mean, you all loved him

32:42.193 --> 32:44.195
all those years
that he was here for you.

32:46.197 --> 32:50.200
I just think that

32:50.201 --> 32:55.706
if you really love your father,
you'll love him now.

33:02.213 --> 33:04.715
22,996.

33:04.716 --> 33:05.716
22,997.

33:05.717 --> 33:07.718
22,998.

33:07.719 --> 33:09.219
22,999.

33:09.220 --> 33:10.721
23,000.

33:10.722 --> 33:11.723
It's Thursday.

33:15.226 --> 33:16.727
I can't go on like this.

33:16.728 --> 33:19.730
I can't go on
being alone like this.

33:19.731 --> 33:23.233
That's why I have
to keep talking to myself.

33:23.234 --> 33:25.736
Oh, if only a bird
would fly in to keep me company.

33:25.737 --> 33:27.738
It would be so nice.

33:27.739 --> 33:30.240
I remember
how it helped Burt Lancaster.

33:30.241 --> 33:32.743
Roommate, Tate.

33:32.744 --> 33:34.745
Oh, thank God.
Somebody to talk to.

33:34.746 --> 33:35.746
Hello.

33:35.747 --> 33:37.748
Welcome.

33:37.749 --> 33:39.750
Oh, you don't know
how happy I am to see you.

33:39.751 --> 33:41.752
You just don't know
how happy I am.

33:41.753 --> 33:43.754
Shut up.

33:43.755 --> 33:46.757
Oh, well, yes, of course.
I'm sorry.

33:46.758 --> 33:48.258
You're not happy to be here.

33:48.259 --> 33:49.259
That's terrible of me to say

33:49.260 --> 33:51.261
that I'm happy that you're here.

33:51.262 --> 33:53.764
You see, what I mean is...

33:53.765 --> 33:55.767
Uh... Oh, excuse me,
that's mine.

33:57.769 --> 33:59.270
Not anymore, it ain't.

34:01.272 --> 34:03.774
Ah, yes. I see.

34:03.775 --> 34:04.775
Well, what will I shave with?

34:04.776 --> 34:06.777
Every morning,

34:06.778 --> 34:08.279
I'll rub your face
against the wall.

34:14.786 --> 34:18.288
You'll rub my face
against the wall?

34:18.289 --> 34:19.289
Oh. Oh, I see.

34:19.290 --> 34:21.792
They've given me
a funny roommate.

34:23.795 --> 34:24.795
I like that.

34:24.795 --> 34:26.295
You'll rub my face
against the w...

34:26.297 --> 34:29.299
I want that tooth.
The gold one.

34:29.300 --> 34:31.802
Open up.

34:31.803 --> 34:34.304
You mean mine?
My gold tooth? Mine?

34:34.304 --> 34:36.306
You're a funny fellow.
I like your sense of humor.

34:36.306 --> 34:38.308
What do you expect me to do?
Rip it out?

34:38.309 --> 34:39.810
Right.

34:39.811 --> 34:42.312
What are you in for?

34:42.313 --> 34:45.315
Murder. I'm wanted
in 10 states.

34:46.818 --> 34:49.319
Murder? Oh, my God!

34:49.320 --> 34:50.821
Who did they put me in with?

34:50.822 --> 34:52.322
Guard! Guard!

34:52.322 --> 34:54.324
What are you in here for?

34:54.324 --> 34:55.326
Huh?

35:03.334 --> 35:04.334
Murder.

35:04.335 --> 35:05.836
Ho, ho, ho!

35:05.837 --> 35:06.837
[LAUGHING]

35:06.838 --> 35:07.838
What's so funny?

35:07.839 --> 35:09.840
Murder. You?

35:09.841 --> 35:11.341
That's right.

35:11.342 --> 35:14.845
What did you do?
Bore somebody to death?

35:20.351 --> 35:21.852
Yeah...

35:23.855 --> 35:24.855
Aah!

35:24.856 --> 35:26.356
What's so funny?

35:26.357 --> 35:28.358
You.

35:28.359 --> 35:29.359
Oh, no. Not you.

35:29.360 --> 35:31.361
No, no. Uh, what you said.

35:31.362 --> 35:33.864
That cute little thing
you said about my being boring.

35:33.865 --> 35:35.365
You laugh when
I tell you to laugh,

35:35.366 --> 35:36.367
you understand?

35:40.872 --> 35:43.875
All right. Entertain me. Dance.

35:48.379 --> 35:49.379
I beg your pardon?

35:49.380 --> 35:50.380
Dance.

35:50.381 --> 35:52.382
Dance?

35:52.383 --> 35:53.383
You mean...

35:53.384 --> 35:54.885
La-de-da dance?

35:54.886 --> 35:56.386
I mean dance now

35:56.387 --> 35:57.888
or you're going to have trouble
walking later.

35:57.889 --> 35:58.889
Oh, yes, dance, dance.

35:58.890 --> 35:59.890
That kind of dance.

35:59.891 --> 36:01.892
Uh...
Well, I may be a little rusty.

36:01.893 --> 36:03.393
What would you like?

36:03.394 --> 36:04.394
Tap? Ballet?

36:04.395 --> 36:07.397
A little Martha Graham, maybe?

36:07.398 --> 36:10.400
I can't dance.
I can't just dance.

36:10.401 --> 36:12.402
I...

36:12.403 --> 36:13.404
I need music.

36:14.405 --> 36:15.405
Sing.

36:17.408 --> 36:21.912
♪ Picture you upon my knee ♪

36:21.913 --> 36:25.416
♪ Tea for two And two for tea ♪

36:39.430 --> 36:41.432
Don't touch me.

36:42.433 --> 36:43.433
Who?

36:43.434 --> 36:46.437
You lay one finger on me,
and I'll break it off.

36:47.939 --> 36:49.439
What?

36:49.440 --> 36:51.942
Coming home at 4 in the morning.

36:51.943 --> 36:53.443
I was working.

36:53.444 --> 36:56.947
Really?
What are you, a night watchman?

36:56.948 --> 36:57.949
Dumb.

37:01.953 --> 37:03.453
Uh, Mary,

37:03.454 --> 37:04.454
uh, what are you talking about?

37:04.455 --> 37:06.456
What am I talking about?
What am I talking about?

37:06.457 --> 37:07.457
I will tell you

37:07.458 --> 37:08.959
what I'm talking about.

37:08.960 --> 37:09.960
I am talking about

37:09.961 --> 37:11.962
all these weeks
we haven't made love

37:11.963 --> 37:14.464
because you've been working
until 4:00 in the morning.

37:14.465 --> 37:16.466
And I was stupid enough
to believe it.

37:16.467 --> 37:19.469
Well, now I know
what you've really been doing

37:19.470 --> 37:21.471
till 4:00 in the morning, Burt.

37:21.472 --> 37:22.973
I figured it out,

37:22.974 --> 37:23.975
and it's not work.

37:30.481 --> 37:32.482
What is it?

37:32.483 --> 37:33.483
You don't know?

37:33.484 --> 37:34.484
No.

37:34.485 --> 37:36.987
How can you not know?
You're the one that's doing it.

37:36.988 --> 37:38.488
Doing what?

37:38.489 --> 37:39.489
Having an affair.

37:39.490 --> 37:40.491
I am?

37:41.492 --> 37:42.493
Yes.

37:44.495 --> 37:45.495
With who?

37:45.496 --> 37:47.497
I don't know who.

37:47.498 --> 37:48.999
Well, I mean,
am I having a good time?

37:51.502 --> 37:53.003
Why can't you just admit it?

37:53.004 --> 37:54.504
Because it's not true, Mary.

37:54.505 --> 37:55.505
Good night, Mary.

37:58.509 --> 38:00.010
You are going to sleep?

38:00.011 --> 38:01.012
Yes.

38:03.014 --> 38:07.517
You have got some nerve,
you know that?

38:07.518 --> 38:09.019
You kill my husband,

38:09.020 --> 38:10.520
you become impotent,

38:10.521 --> 38:13.523
then you become invisible
and get yourself committed.

38:13.524 --> 38:15.025
I stand by you
through all of that,

38:15.026 --> 38:18.029
and as soon as you get better,
you go out and have an affair.

38:19.530 --> 38:20.530
Oh yeah? Oh yeah?

38:20.531 --> 38:22.032
Well, if I'm out
having an affair

38:22.033 --> 38:23.033
till 4:00
in the morning,

38:23.034 --> 38:24.534
why, when I get home,

38:24.535 --> 38:26.036
do I wake you up to make love?

38:26.037 --> 38:28.039
Come on, why in the world
would I do that?

38:29.540 --> 38:30.540
To trick me.

38:30.541 --> 38:32.542
Uh, that's...
Good night, Mary.

38:32.543 --> 38:36.046
It's just like the married man
who was having an affair

38:36.047 --> 38:38.548
and had to... to eat two dinners
every night,

38:38.549 --> 38:41.551
one with his mistress
and one with his wife.

38:41.552 --> 38:44.054
Of course, he became a fat slob,
and they both dumped him.

38:44.055 --> 38:48.058
Served him right.

38:48.059 --> 38:51.561
Wake up, Burt!

38:51.562 --> 38:52.562
What are you doing?

38:52.563 --> 38:53.563
I'm sleeping downstairs.

38:53.564 --> 38:54.564
Why?

38:54.565 --> 38:55.565
Because I'm getting mad.

38:55.566 --> 38:56.566
You can't be mad.

38:56.567 --> 38:58.568
What do you mean I can't be mad?

38:58.569 --> 39:00.070
You're the one
that's having the affair.

39:00.071 --> 39:01.071
I'm the one that's mad.

39:01.072 --> 39:03.573
Uh, you, Mary, are a dope.

39:03.574 --> 39:05.075
Oh!

39:05.076 --> 39:07.577
That's what you are.
A real dope.

39:07.578 --> 39:10.580
First of all,
I'm not having an affair.

39:10.581 --> 39:14.584
I am not having an affair,
nor do I want to have an affair.

39:14.585 --> 39:15.585
And if I was having an affair,

39:15.586 --> 39:17.587
I would be
a hell of a lot smarter

39:17.588 --> 39:19.589
than to have it
at 4:00 in the morning

39:19.590 --> 39:20.590
and tell you I was working.

39:20.591 --> 39:22.592
I'd have my affair

39:22.593 --> 39:24.094
at a totally different
time of day,

39:24.095 --> 39:26.596
a time of day
when you wouldn't be suspicious,

39:26.597 --> 39:29.599
and I wouldn't be so sleepy.

39:29.600 --> 39:33.103
Yeah, I have been coming home
at 4:00 in the morning, Mary,

39:33.104 --> 39:35.105
because I've been killing myself
working to make a better life

39:35.106 --> 39:36.106
for us.

39:36.107 --> 39:37.607
That's what I've been doing.

39:37.608 --> 39:40.110
All day, I'm up in the girders

39:40.111 --> 39:41.611
supervising every job.

39:41.612 --> 39:43.113
At night I'm in the office,

39:43.114 --> 39:44.114
uh-huh,
doing paper work.

39:44.115 --> 39:46.616
I got bills, payrolls,
invoices...

39:46.617 --> 39:48.618
Uh, don't cry, Mary,
like you always do when I'm mad

39:48.619 --> 39:50.120
so I'll stop yelling,

39:50.121 --> 39:51.621
because it's not going to work.

39:51.622 --> 39:52.622
[SNIFFLES]

39:52.623 --> 39:55.625
[MOANS] Yeow! I knew it.
I hate it.

39:55.626 --> 39:59.129
I can't help it.

39:59.130 --> 40:01.131
I've been so upset
about everything...

40:01.132 --> 40:02.632
Danny, Jodie, the Tates.

40:02.633 --> 40:05.635
I... I don't know what to think
anymore, and that's why...

40:05.636 --> 40:06.636
[SNIFFLES]

40:06.637 --> 40:07.638
Oh...

40:10.641 --> 40:12.642
Blow your nose.

40:12.643 --> 40:14.144
[SNIFFS]

40:14.145 --> 40:15.646
[GROANS] Blow out, Mary, not in.

40:18.149 --> 40:19.649
I'm sorry.

40:19.650 --> 40:22.652
I'm sorry I said all those
terrible things, but...

40:22.653 --> 40:24.154
everyone else I love

40:24.155 --> 40:27.657
is either in jail
or getting out of jail

40:27.658 --> 40:29.159
or getting married or moving out

40:29.160 --> 40:32.162
and so...
I figured why not you too.

40:32.163 --> 40:34.164
I mean, every time
you look at me,

40:34.165 --> 40:35.665
I am crying.

40:35.666 --> 40:37.167
I'm not exactly

40:37.168 --> 40:40.170
the most enchanting woman
in the world

40:40.171 --> 40:41.672
these days.

40:43.174 --> 40:44.174
You are to me.

40:44.175 --> 40:46.176
How can I be?

40:46.177 --> 40:47.677
Because I love you.

40:47.678 --> 40:49.679
I don't know why.

40:49.680 --> 40:50.680
Oh...

40:50.681 --> 40:52.182
You... You don't know why?

40:52.183 --> 40:53.183
You?

40:53.184 --> 40:54.685
You blow your nose in
instead of out.

40:55.686 --> 40:56.686
You pull all the covers

40:56.687 --> 40:58.188
over to your side

40:58.189 --> 40:59.189
when you sleep.

40:59.190 --> 41:01.191
You take food off my plate,

41:01.192 --> 41:03.693
and you have never, ever,
ironed one of my shirts

41:03.694 --> 41:04.694
correctly.

41:04.695 --> 41:06.697
And I think that
that's all adorable.

41:08.699 --> 41:10.700
If I didn't love you,

41:10.701 --> 41:13.703
I would have divorced you
by now.

41:13.704 --> 41:15.705
And that's how I know.

41:15.706 --> 41:16.707
I just love you.

41:19.710 --> 41:21.711
Burt...

41:21.712 --> 41:23.213
I'm a dope.

41:25.716 --> 41:27.217
I love you.

41:32.223 --> 41:33.723
I iron your shirts terrible?

41:33.724 --> 41:35.225
Yeah. It's all right.

41:35.226 --> 41:36.726
No, no.
I want the truth.

41:36.727 --> 41:38.228
I do an awful job?

41:38.229 --> 41:39.729
Yeah, Mary,
it's really terrible.

41:39.730 --> 41:41.231
Shirts are not so easy.

41:41.232 --> 41:42.232
I know.

41:42.233 --> 41:43.733
They have collars.
Did you know that?

41:43.734 --> 41:45.235
You should try
ironing the collars...

41:45.236 --> 41:46.736
It's all right.
Mary, stop, don't.

41:46.737 --> 41:47.777
We'll send the shirts out.

41:54.245 --> 41:56.746
[FEEBLY]
♪ You start to bake A sugar cake ♪

41:56.747 --> 41:59.249
♪ For me to take
For all the boys to see... ♪

41:59.250 --> 42:00.750
Tate.

42:00.751 --> 42:03.253
[LOUDER]
♪ We will raise a family ♪

42:03.254 --> 42:04.754
♪ A boy for you ♪

42:04.755 --> 42:06.256
♪ A girl for me ♪

42:06.257 --> 42:10.760
♪ Can't you see
How happy we will be? ♪

42:10.761 --> 42:11.761
Jess.

42:11.762 --> 42:13.263
Chester.

42:13.264 --> 42:16.266
It's so nice to see you
enjoying prison life.

42:16.267 --> 42:19.269
I mean, there I was at home
worried sick about him,

42:19.270 --> 42:21.271
and here he is
singing and dancing.

42:21.272 --> 42:23.273
I brought you some food.

42:23.274 --> 42:24.774
If I'd known you had a roommate,

42:24.775 --> 42:26.276
I would have brought more.

42:26.277 --> 42:27.277
Oh, that's okay.

42:27.278 --> 42:28.278
He's not having any.

42:28.279 --> 42:29.279
Oh? Why?

42:29.280 --> 42:30.280
Upset stomach.

42:30.281 --> 42:31.782
Oh, dear.

42:34.725 --> 42:36.286
[WHISPERS] They put me in
with a killer.

42:36.287 --> 42:39.289
Well, of course they did, dear.

42:39.290 --> 42:41.292
I imagine they do it
like computer dating.

42:43.794 --> 42:46.296
You two
have a great deal in common.

42:47.798 --> 42:49.299
Jess, I'm not a killer.

42:49.300 --> 42:52.802
Now, Chester, I know you don't
think of yourself as a killer.

42:52.803 --> 42:55.805
I'm sure you consider yourself
primarily a stockbroker.

42:55.806 --> 42:58.308
Nonetheless, Chester...

42:58.309 --> 43:01.811
I... I did kill Peter.
There's no denying that.

43:01.812 --> 43:03.813
It's just...

43:03.814 --> 43:04.814
it's all so confusing.

43:04.815 --> 43:07.817
I know it is, dear.

43:07.818 --> 43:11.321
And we know there's more to this
than meets the eye,

43:11.322 --> 43:13.323
and I want you to know, Chester,

43:13.324 --> 43:15.825
we're all standing by you.

43:15.826 --> 43:17.327
Thank you, Jess.

43:17.328 --> 43:20.330
Now, while you're here,

43:20.331 --> 43:22.833
I want you to volunteer for work
in the prison laundry.

43:24.835 --> 43:25.835
The laundry?

43:25.836 --> 43:28.338
Mm. That way you'll come out
with a skill.

43:31.342 --> 43:34.844
You see, darling,
when you do get out,

43:34.845 --> 43:37.847
I think the idea
of going back to Wall Street

43:37.848 --> 43:38.848
is out of the question.

43:38.849 --> 43:40.850
Time's up.

43:40.851 --> 43:42.852
Oh, dear. Goodbye.

43:42.853 --> 43:44.854
I'll see you next week.

43:44.855 --> 43:45.855
Ta.

43:50.361 --> 43:52.362
You can forget about
seeing her next week.

43:52.363 --> 43:53.863
What do you mean?

43:53.864 --> 43:55.866
You ain't gonna be here
next week.

43:57.368 --> 43:59.869
Oh, no. Oh, no.
Please don't.

43:59.870 --> 44:02.872
Oh, please,
I beg you. No....

44:02.873 --> 44:04.874
Get up off your knees, Tate,

44:04.875 --> 44:05.875
for God's sake.

44:05.876 --> 44:07.377
I can't believe you're in here

44:07.378 --> 44:09.379
for murder.

44:09.380 --> 44:11.881
Listen. Tomorrow,
I'm escaping.

44:11.882 --> 44:14.884
You are?

44:14.885 --> 44:15.886
I'll miss you.

44:17.388 --> 44:21.391
You're coming with me, Tate,

44:21.392 --> 44:22.392
as a shield.

44:22.393 --> 44:24.394
This way, when they start
shooting at me,

44:24.395 --> 44:25.895
I got you to put in front of me.

44:25.896 --> 44:27.397
I'm not going.
You are.

44:27.398 --> 44:29.399
I'll tell the guard.

44:29.400 --> 44:30.600
[MOCKING] I'll tell the guard.

44:32.282 --> 44:33.403
You're coming with me, Tate!

44:33.404 --> 44:35.405
I am not.
You are too.

44:35.406 --> 44:37.407
No way.
You're coming, Tate.

44:37.408 --> 44:38.408
Absolutely not.

44:38.409 --> 44:39.409
Then I'll kill you.

44:39.410 --> 44:40.911
When do we leave?

44:44.915 --> 44:45.916
[DOORBELL RINGS]

44:48.419 --> 44:49.419
Hi.

44:49.420 --> 44:50.920
Well, did you see Elaine?

44:50.921 --> 44:52.422
Yeah. I did everything
you told me to.

44:52.423 --> 44:53.923
Exactly like we rehearsed?

44:53.924 --> 44:54.924
You know it.

44:54.925 --> 44:56.426
You told her
that you were impotent?

44:56.427 --> 44:57.927
Right.

44:57.928 --> 45:00.430
I told her that, uh,
I had this family disease,

45:00.431 --> 45:02.432
and I finally just caught it
the other day,

45:02.433 --> 45:03.933
and that is she wanted
to marry me,

45:03.934 --> 45:05.435
she'd have absolutely
nothing to look forward to

45:05.436 --> 45:07.437
in the bed department.
Great.

45:07.438 --> 45:08.439
So what happened?

45:11.442 --> 45:13.944
[SIGHS] Girl knows
a lot of tricks.

45:22.453 --> 45:23.453
Danny.

45:23.454 --> 45:25.955
She took me by surprise.

45:25.956 --> 45:28.458
So now we have to pick out
presents for the ushers.

45:28.459 --> 45:31.461
Yeah.

45:31.462 --> 45:32.462
Hey, why should I worry?

45:32.463 --> 45:34.464
I mean at the rate
she's got me going,

45:34.465 --> 45:36.466
I won't live to see October.

45:36.467 --> 45:38.468
I gotta go to work.
I'll see you later.

45:38.469 --> 45:39.969
All right. Give my love to Mom.

45:39.970 --> 45:41.471
Yeah.

45:41.472 --> 45:45.475
Oh, did I just miss
a very popular sports figure?

45:45.476 --> 45:46.976
It happened to have been Danny.

45:46.977 --> 45:48.478
Really?

45:48.479 --> 45:50.480
You mean it wasn't
the Rose Bowl Queen?

45:50.481 --> 45:51.981
Carol, what is it with you?

45:51.982 --> 45:53.483
Nothing.

45:53.484 --> 45:54.484
I just had no idea

45:54.485 --> 45:55.985
that when we took
an apartment together

45:55.986 --> 45:57.487
it would be like living
in the Continental baths.

45:57.488 --> 45:59.489
Carol, I've had it with you.

45:59.490 --> 46:00.490
We had an arrangement.

46:00.491 --> 46:02.492
I told you I was going
to live my own life.

46:02.493 --> 46:04.994
I know. Look it, I'm sorry.

46:04.995 --> 46:07.497
It's just that I never see you.

46:07.498 --> 46:10.500
I saw more of you
when we weren't living together.

46:10.501 --> 46:12.502
Jodie, I just miss you,
that's all.

46:12.503 --> 46:14.003
I miss spending time with you.

46:14.004 --> 46:15.505
Please, don't be mad.

46:18.509 --> 46:20.009
Listen, how about I apologize

46:20.010 --> 46:22.512
by fixing us a really
terrific dinner tonight?

46:22.513 --> 46:24.013
I'll fix your
favorite meal, okay?

46:24.014 --> 46:25.014
What's your favorite meal?

46:25.015 --> 46:28.518
Or we could go out,
if you'd rather go out.

46:28.519 --> 46:29.519
My treat, okay?

46:29.520 --> 46:32.021
Oh, or I could cook. Whatever.

46:32.022 --> 46:33.523
Uh, I can't tonight.

46:35.025 --> 46:38.528
Oh. Oh, okay. Sure.

46:38.529 --> 46:40.029
Some other time, then.

46:40.030 --> 46:42.031
Another night.
There's lots of nights.

46:42.032 --> 46:43.533
Carol, is something wrong?

46:43.534 --> 46:45.535
No. No.

46:45.536 --> 46:46.536
You're sure?

46:46.537 --> 46:48.538
Right. Sure.

46:48.539 --> 46:50.541
Okay. I've got to get dressed.

46:54.044 --> 46:55.044
Carol, uh...

46:55.045 --> 46:56.546
you're sure nothing's wrong?

46:56.547 --> 47:00.050
I am positive
there is nothing wrong.

47:06.056 --> 47:09.559
There's nothing wrong,
nothing at all.

47:09.560 --> 47:12.563
I'm just...
pregnant with your child.

47:23.073 --> 47:26.576
<i>And now,</i>
<i>coming attractions of</i> Soap.

47:26.577 --> 47:28.077
[WHISPERS] Go ahead.
Jump, Tate.

47:28.078 --> 47:29.579
After you.

47:29.580 --> 47:30.581
Okay.

47:32.082 --> 47:34.584
I always thought I'd love
the girl I married.

47:34.585 --> 47:36.085
I always thought
the girl you married

47:36.086 --> 47:37.587
would be a little like me,

47:37.588 --> 47:38.588
but Elaine...

47:38.589 --> 47:40.090
She's a pig.

47:41.592 --> 47:44.093
Hey, you're very pretty.

47:44.094 --> 47:46.095
Listen, you...

47:46.096 --> 47:47.597
If you came up here
intending to rape me,

47:47.598 --> 47:50.600
let me tell you right now
it's not gonna be any fun at all

47:50.601 --> 47:53.102
because I'll spit in your face.

47:53.103 --> 47:54.604
How do you two guys
like working together?

47:54.605 --> 47:55.605
Oh, it's terrific.

47:55.606 --> 47:56.606
Great.

47:56.607 --> 47:58.107
Sure. One's got a flea brain.

47:58.108 --> 47:59.609
The invisible man's got
none at all.

48:01.111 --> 48:02.612
[YELPING]

48:04.615 --> 48:06.115
Father Tim,
what are you doing here?

48:06.116 --> 48:08.618
I'm getting married.
Didn't you know, Father?

48:08.619 --> 48:12.622
You mean priests can marry now?

48:12.623 --> 48:14.124
I don't believe this.

48:16.126 --> 48:18.127
Don't sit! Don't sit!

48:18.128 --> 48:20.630
Uh, Sally?

48:20.631 --> 48:21.631
Ah...

48:21.632 --> 48:23.633
Uh, Sally...
what are you doing back there?

48:23.634 --> 48:24.634
Nothing.

48:24.635 --> 48:26.636
That's a nice touch.
A real nice touch.

48:26.637 --> 48:28.638
A little hair massage and a...

48:28.639 --> 48:29.639
Ooh...

48:29.640 --> 48:31.641
That's nice...
Whoo! Oh, hey, ho!

48:31.642 --> 48:34.143
What about sex?

48:34.144 --> 48:36.145
Carol, I promise you
that if we get married,

48:36.146 --> 48:37.647
I'll never
touch another man again.

48:37.648 --> 48:40.650
Jodie is going to be a father.

48:40.651 --> 48:43.153
Dennis is pregnant?

